<p>

Explanation:
<list>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

 "no" means a file is not read by a shell at all.</entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

 "yes" means a file is always read by a shell.</entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

 "login" means a file is read if the shell is a login shell.</entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

 "n/login" means a file is read if the shell is not a login shell.</entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

 "int." means a file is read if the shell is interactive.</entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

 "i.login" means a file is read if the shell is an interactive login shell.</entry>
</list>
</p>

